Main Features Ranges:¶

  • Date & Time: year-month-day, hour:minute
  • Temperature : -13 to 88 F
  • Humidity : 1 to 100 %
  • Windspeed : 0 to 21.8 m/s
  • Visibility : 0 to 10 km
  • Pressure : 982.5 to 1042 mm Hg
  • Total KW : 0 to 3.36 kWh

Preliminary Observations: ¶

  • Meter4_data is having zero values , it shall be removed in order not to affect the model
  • Need to drop repeated columns [icon,summary]
  • Need to drop Zero valued columns
  • The datasets shall be merged into one dataset, but before merging, Time observations need to be unifed to "Hourly" basis

In [32]:
#Standardization to make all features on the same scale 

Y=KW_VS_Weather['KW TOTAL']# label that I want to predict

Prediction Models Conclusion: ¶

The KNN model predicted well the electricity consumption , However The model did not predict very well the consumption during the holiday period (from 15 dec onwards). This might be due to the houses were not occupied during the holiday season by their owners as usual, which explains the reduction in electricity consumption

## Project Conclusions: The weather featues has correlation and impact on electrical consumption of home appliances. The main weather feature is humidity, which has more influnence on electrical consumption than temperature. Therefore, in order to have more savings in electrical consumption, humidity need to be controlled within the house.
